article.headline: Longwood 111, Montreat 62
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- A pair of career-high performances -- Aaron Mitchell's 25 points and Mark Parker's 17 -- helped Longwood rout NAIA visitor Montreat 111-62 Monday night. Longwood (3-2) won its ninth straight home game, and is averaging 103.3 points a game in this season's three contests on its floor. Parker did most of his damage from long range, making 5 of 6 from the 3-point line and beyond. Antwan Carter did damage on both ends, scoring 15 points and grabbing 15 rebounds as the Lancers outrebounded the Cavaliers 54-35. Longwood led for more than 37 of the 40 minutes, outscored Montreat 58-30 in the second half, and led by 54 points when Jeylani Dublin's jumper made it 108-54 with 2:11 left. Matt Rushing led the Cavaliers (2-3) with 12 points.
